Okay - this is a very minor nit, but since I just took about 20 minutes to figure it out, what's a few more minutes?

In your online help for wiki markup items, you have a section for links that is pretty complete.  One item it seems to be missing, however, is how to link to another Jira issue.  I would add the \[|key-nnn\] notation to the first row of the Links help table along with \[#anchor\] and \[^attachment\].

